  "text": "Male Sprague-Dawley rats (300-350 g) were anesthetized with pentobarbital sodium (50 mg/kg ip), and an intraperitoneal catheter was inserted to allow delivery of further anesthetic as needed. The sciatic nerve was dissected free, cut, and placed within a bipolar platinum electrode. Rats were mounted in a specially designed NMR probe with the Achilles tendon attached to a force transducer as described previously [CITATION_1] . Stimulation voltage and muscle length were adjusted to produce maximum twitch force.",
